children.characters: Product Intersections

children.name: Text Description
children.characters: Intersections are pivotal points where two product areas converge, facilitating communication, data sharing, and providing users with pathways to explore additional features within Pendo. These intersections hold significant value in our product design ethos as they enable seamless integration and enhance user experience beyond individual product silos.

children.name: Text
Section Title / Heading 2
children.characters: Why are intersections important and how can we leverage them effectively?

children.name: Text
children.characters:
At Pendo, we recognise that we're crafting experiences for the same user base, addressing varied problems across different product areas. It's imperative to transcend product boundaries and foster discoverability across our platform. An intersection occurs when a feature extends beyond its designated product area, adding value to another area in a timely and proactive manner. Essentially, it's about solving diverse user needs within the Pendo experience. Intersections typically manifest in three common ways:

Value-add: Providing users with additional information and insights.
Alternative view: Offering specific views, segments, filtered data, or synthesized information to help users pinpoint relevant details.
Re-use: Leveraging existing product areas to enrich the context of your own.

children.name: Section Title / Heading 2
children.characters: How can I influence my intersections?

children.name: Text
children.characters:
As designers, we're entrusted with exploring and ideating these intersections during the design process. Similar to crafting any other design pattern, we aim to create intersections that are recognisable and intuitive. While the benefits of intersections are substantial, it's crucial to ensure their relevance and avoid unnecessary clutter. At Pendo, we prioritise meaningful interactions that enhance user experiences. Here are three questions to guide your intersection design:

Is this intersection valuable?
Am I introducing this intersection at the right place and using appropriate UI elements?
Does the user require this intersection to accomplish their task, and does it disrupt their current journey?
Can I provide adequate context for this intersection?

children.name: Section Title / Heading 2
children.characters: What key considerations should be addressed before developing intersections?

children.name: Text
children.characters:
Before diving into intersection development, it's essential to address several key questions to ensure their effectiveness:

Is there a need for users to quickly transition in and out of their workflow?
Yes, providing users with the option to navigate back and forth between intersections is recommended. While there may be alternative considerations, such as integrating features from other product areas, allowing users to seamlessly exit and return to their original workflow is generally preferred.

Should contextual information or help be provided?
Adding an intersection without context can lead to confusion or conflict with existing features. Consider including informational tags or titles to clarify the purpose of the intersection and guide users on how to navigate through it.

Should intersections be rebuilt within your product area?
No, it's advisable to avoid duplicating intersections within your product area. Instead, collaborate with colleagues from the relevant product team, tech leads, or product managers to explore how to extend your product's capabilities to integrate with other areas organically.

How do you balance recommendations versus making features integral parts of intersections?
If intersections become integral components of the product and users frequently engage with them, consider incorporating relevant features directly into your product area. Alternatively, if the value lies in offering add-on features, linking to them can suffice. Striking the right balance depends on the user's needs and the strategic goals of your product area.

children.name: Section Title / Heading 2
children.characters: Examples

children.name: Text
children.characters: Here are several examples of intersections currently either in development or already integrated into our product. Each of these intersections varies in functionality but consistently adheres to our established design patterns.

children.name: Section title / Heading 3
children.characters: Guide Polls

children.name: Text
children.characters: Guide poll, initially a native feature in the Guide product area, revealed potential beyond its original scope, as discoverability unveiled use cases for its integration into Discover. This integration not only facilitated gathering feedback but also enhanced the user experience by layering AI-generated summaries for comprehensive data-to-text overviews.

children.name: Section title / Heading 3
children.characters: Suggested Replays and recommendatiosn

children.name: Text
children.characters: Session insight, was designed to compile user data behaviour alongside watching replays, now showcases its versatility by seamlessly integrating with our existing features. Furthermore, recommendations take on a cohesive role, empowering users to take action effortlessly after watching sessions.

children.name: Section title / Heading 3
children.characters: Watch replays from discover

children.name: Text
children.characters: The intersection "Watch Replays from Discover" bridges the functionality of two distinct product areas, Discover and Replays, within our platform. By enabling users to access replays directly from the Discover interface, we streamline the user journey, enhancing convenience and efficiency. This integration offers users the opportunity to explore recorded sessions seamlessly while browsing through Discover's insights and recommendations. With this feature, users can delve deeper into session replays without disrupting their workflow, fostering a more cohesive and immersive user experience overall.

children.name: Section title / Heading 3
children.characters: Tag details on hover

children.name: Text
children.characters: The intersection "Tooltip Metrics" leverages the synergy between event selection and contextual information delivery through tooltips, enriching user interactions with insights drawn from product analytics data. By integrating tooltips that dynamically display relevant data when hovering over selected events, we enhance the user's understanding of metrics within the context of their actions. This intersection seamlessly integrates page data from our product analytics, empowering users with real-time insights to make informed decisions and optimize their workflow effectively.
